What is the Home Appliance Market?
The home appliance market encompasses electrical and mechanical devices designed to perform various household functions, including cooking, cleaning, food preservation, and climate control. These products are broadly categorized into major appliances (white goods), small appliances, and consumer electronics. Major appliances include refrigeration equipment, home laundry appliances, dishwashers, air conditioners, and large cooking appliances that form the core of modern household infrastructure. These essential devices have evolved from basic functionality to sophisticated systems integrating artificial intelligence, Internet of Things (IoT) connectivity, and energy management features that significantly enhance user convenience, efficiency, and lifestyle quality.

